.DS_Store
.Rhistory
.RData
Rplots.pdf

# --- Raw data ---
# Primary source data lives under data_raw/{italy,france}/. Most of it is
# either shipped in the repo (Italian govt primary data, Cremaschi panel) or
# downloaded by the pipeline. Default: ignore everything, then re-include the
# specific subtrees that should ship.
data_raw/*
!data_raw/italy/
data_raw/italy/*
!data_raw/italy/electoral_panel_dataset.dta
!data_raw/italy/cremaschi_replication/
!data_raw/italy/cremaschi_replication/**
!data_raw/italy/ministero_interno/
!data_raw/italy/ministero_interno/unioni_comuni_ministero_2020.csv
!data_raw/italy/opencivitas/
!data_raw/italy/opencivitas/Ind_FC20*.csv
!data_raw/italy/opencivitas/Metadati_Enti_2022.xlsx
# Italy 2022 elections are downloaded by the pipeline — do not ship
# France raw data is downloaded by the pipeline — do not ship

# --- Processed data (regenerated by make) ---
data_processed/

# --- Generated outputs (reproducible via make) ---
output/figures/italy/
output/figures/france/
output/csvs/italy/
output/csvs/france/
# Tables are also regenerated, EXCEPT tab_compliance_three (hand-maintained:
# the underlying CSVs are produced by code/italy_mechanism/ but the table
# assembly is manual).
output/tables/italy/*
!output/tables/italy/tab_compliance_three.tex
output/tables/france/

# --- LaTeX build artifacts ---
# The three compiled PDFs (size_gradient_report.pdf,
# size_gradient_report_appendix.pdf, size_gradient_report_with_appendix.pdf)
# are intentionally tracked in this repo as convenience copies; rebuilding
# them via `make` will overwrite the working copies but they will continue
# to be tracked.
*.aux
*.log
*.out
*.synctex.gz
*.fls
*.fdb_latexmk
*.bbl
*.blg
*.toc
